  "ComponentID": "CH32V003",
  "ComponentType": "32-bit RISC-V Microcontroller (MCU)",
  "Description": "The CH32V003 is an industrial-grade general-purpose microcontroller based on the Qingke RISC-V2A core (RV32EC ISA). It operates at up to 48 MHz, supports wide-voltage operation (2.7V to 5.5V), and features low-power modes, a single-wire debug interface, and small package options. Key peripherals include 16KB of Code Flash, 2KB of SRAM, a 10-bit ADC with up to 8 external channels, one operational amplifier/comparator, multiple timers (including an advanced timer for motor control), and standard communication interfaces (USART, I2C, SPI). It is designed for cost-sensitive embedded applications requiring efficient processing and connectivity.",
